Police have dispersed a small group of students who held a night vigil at the Prospect Street gate. CAPE TOWN Calm has been restored to the University of Pretoria s Hatfield campus following morning protests in which students set two vehicles and a guard house on fire.Under the banner of Fees Must Fall , students held an overnight vigil outside campus before clashes broke out with police.It appears the academic programme has resumed at the university s Hatfield campus after the earlier protest.Police have dispersed the small group of students who held a night vigil at the Prospect Street gate.There is a heavy police contingent both in and around the campus.(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)